observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Management agreed to:
Direct the MPDO to incorporate specific PPAs in the AIP and prepare a supplemental AIP;
Seek authorization from the SB thru a Resolution for the COVID-19 expenses charged against the lump-sum appropriation presented in generic terms;
Direct the MBO to ensure proper authorization of PPAs with generic terms, before certifying the Obligation Request; and
Require the MA to require SB Resolution before certifying the completeness and propriety of supporting documents.

We recommended that Management strengthen its monitoring controls by requiring the MDRRM Office and Municipal Health Office to:

a.) Ensure proper coordination among the Offices concerning the receipt and distribution of Donations In-Kind;

b.) Ensure issuance of Acknowledgment Receipts to all future receipts of donations in-kind to confirm that donations are properly recorded and accounted for; 

c.) Ensure that all future issuances of donated items are properly supported with Issuance Form for In-Kind Donations or any document/record to prove receipt by and distribution to the intended beneficiaries; and

d.) Determine the inventory of remaining undistributed items, if there is any, for recording in the Registry of Donated Relief Goods for DRRM.

Municipal Accountant to-
Include in the Inventory account all Accountable Forms (with and without money value) as provided in Section 175 of GAM Vol. 1 to ensure completeness of the items included in the Financial Statements;
Record the purchases as Inventory and adhere to the provisions of Section 181 on the proper measurement of the Inventory at year-end to ensure accuracy of the amounts reported;
Prepare an adjusting entry to correct the balance of the affected accounts; and
Municipal Treasurer to-
Prepare a separate logbook for Accountable Forms held for consumption/distribution from those held for sale for proper recording and monitoring of the assets.

Direct the BAC Secretariat to immediately comply with the GPPB Online Portal's posting requirement for Emergency Procurement under Republic Act 11469 (Bayanihan to Heal as One Act).
Capacitate the BAC Secretariat on the laws, rules and regulations on government procurement;
Require the BAC Secretariat to promote transparency in government procurement by ensuring that the Notices of Award and Purchase Orders for future procurements are posted in accordance with the guidelines prescribed.

Require the Local Finance Committee to ensure that the financial information of Bayanihan Grant to Cities and Municipalities are made available to the public, in adherence to the prescribed guidelines outlined in the Local Budget Circular No. 125;
Expedite the creation of the Municipal Government's Official Website; and
Require the Local Finance Committee to keep themselves updated with the latest provisions and guidelines pertaining to their functions.

Ensure proper coordination among the Offices concerning the receipt and distribution of Donations In-Kind;
Ensure issuance of Acknowledgment Receipts to all future receipts of donations in-kind to confirm that donations are properly recorded and accounted for;
Ensure that all future issuances of donated items are properly supported with Issuance Form for In-Kind Donations or any document/record to prove receipt by and distribution to the intended beneficiaries; and
Determine the inventory of remaining undistributed items, if there is any, for recording in the Registry of Donated Relief Goods for DRRM.

Market Supervisor to-
Update and reconcile its financial records to arrive at the corrected balances as of December 31, 2020;
Furnish the Municipal Accountant with the contract of lease and the schedule of uncollected balance at year-end.
Municipal Accountant to-
Prepare an adjusting entry to record the uncollected balances of rent from stallholders at year-end;
Ensure that succeeding revenues will be recorded on an accrual basis pursuant to Section 41 of GAM for LGUs.
